FT  15 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Ibstock in Pounds 8m Portuguese sale
Ibstock Johnsen, the UK's third largest brickmaker, has sold a 20 per cent
stake in its Portuguese offshoot, Celulose do Caima, for about Pounds 7.9m.
The shares were placed with a number of institutional shareholders in London
and Lisbon. Ibstock retains a 56.3 per cent interest.
Caima, which ran up a pre-tax loss of Pounds 4m for 1992, owns eucalyptus
forests and operates a wood pulp mill. The book value of its net assets at
end-December stood at Pounds 43m.
Proceeds will be used to reduce group borrowings.
